<TITLE> BNP slams second notice on Khaleda </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 8 (bdnews24.com)The opposition BNP has censured a second notice on Khaleda Zia to leave her cantonment house as nothing but persecution of the former prime minister. The military lands and cantonments directorate served Khaleda a modified notice to her on Thursday afternoon, the BNP chairperson's press secretary Maruf Kamal Khan late at night. Khaleda discussed the notice with secretary-general Khandker Delwar Hossain, her lawyers Moudud Ahmed and T H Khan and others, The letter, signed by administrator of military land property, asks to leave the house within 15 days in line with the rule of cantonment land administration. "It is needless to send notice again when the matter is pending with the High Court," Delwar told reporters at his Armanitola home on Friday morning. After two High Court benches declined to hear the BNP chief's appeal against the first notice served on Apr 20, a third bench agreed to hear it on Sunday. "We think the notice has been sent a second time to harass her and to smear her politically," Delwar said. The cabinet cancelled the lease on the 2.72-acre mansion on April 8 on grounds that the leasing process had been faulty and she violated lease terms. "The lawyers have discussed the second notice Thursday night," the secretary-general said. He termed the all-party parliamentary investigation into corruption allegation against him as the chief whip of eighth parliament, 'unprecedented' he said the committee does not have the authority to perform such investigations. b
